Defendant Phillip Barnes in court with attorney Valeria L Taylor.  Kimberly D Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    The Court imposed the following sentence:

Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 3 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 18 months with credit for 13 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 18 months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION. The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.   The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of two (2) years.
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
 - Court imposed 120 days condition time:  60 days time to be served at the House of Correction, with Huber for work; Huber for verifiable medical appointments/counseling (no more than two per week.)  Court STAYED report date to:  7/08/14 by 5:00 p.m.  The Court stayed the additional 60 days to be used at the discretion of the agent for any violations.
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant for his physical or mental health  by a duly licensed physician; taken only as prescribed and only for as long as deemed medically reasonable and necessary;
 - No alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation; follow thru with any treatment recommended;
 - No contact with the Sunglass Hut - North, 2500 North Mayfair Road, Wauwatosa, Wisconsin;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, plus the costs, disbursements and supervision fees.  Should defendant get revoked, Court ordered monies taken from prison funds not to exceed 25%.  Balance to be paid while on extended supervision.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Court set restitution at zero.

